HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 13
By Atchley
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate the Sevier County
High School football team, TSSAA Division I,
Class 5A state champion.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school teams that, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors for this State; and
WHEREAS, the Sevier County High School football team achieved an extraordinary
level of success during the 2024 season, winning the coveted Tennessee Secondary School
Athletic Association (TSSAA) Division I, Class 5A State Football Championship; and
WHEREAS, the Sevier County Smoky Bears vanquished every opponent for an
undefeated season on their way to the BlueCross Bowl championship game on December 6,
2024, at Finley Stadium in Chattanooga, where they beat Page High School in a hard-fought
battle in the title matchup; and
WHEREAS, on their path to the championship game, the Smoky Bears defeated
Knoxville Central 35-12, Powell 25-24, Knoxville West 24-17, Oak Ridge 45-34, and finally Page
27-20, to secure the right to hoist the iconic gold football trophy; and
WHEREAS, the victory saw Sevier County High School claim its second football state
championship in school history, joining the team from 1999, to properly end the 100th year of
Smoky Bears football with a perfect record of 15-0; and
WHEREAS, the 2024 Sevier County Smoky Bears enjoyed the services of an
outstanding coaching staff led by Head Coach Todd Loveday, who instilled in these exceptional
young men a commitment to excellence in all that they do and encouraged maximum effort on
the football field; and
