WHEREAS, state championships are achieved only through hard work, dedication, and
the ability to work together as a team and excel with a cooperative spirit; the Smoky Bears
exhibited each of these rare qualities during their championship season; and
WHEREAS, the football players of Sevier County High School epitomize all that is good
in today's student athletes, as they have achieved the highest level of success on the field while
showing the highest degree of character both on and off the gridiron; they inspired their fellow
students and united the entire community during their triumphant run through the 2024 season;
and
WHEREAS, the dedication, determination, work ethic, and talent of this group of young
men not only made possible a championship football season but also surely bode well for their
success in every future endeavor; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud the football players of
Sevier County High School for serving as exemplars of the high quality of the youth of
Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the players, coaching staff, team support staff,
administrators, cheerleaders, and fans of the Sevier County High School football team on
winning the 2024 TSSAA Division I, Class 5A State Football Championship.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
